org.ftccommunity.ftcxtensible.robot

Class ExtensibleHardwareMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ftccommunity.ftcxtensible.robot.ExtensibleHardwareMap

  • @Alpha
public class ExtensibleHardwareMap
extends java.lang.Object
    The new version of the hardware map that provides a safer use for the hardware map. This prevents client code from unintentionally modifying the devices available for use
    Since:
    0.1
    Author:
    David Sargent

    • Method Detail

      • rebuild

        public void rebuild(@NotNull
                    com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.HardwareMap hwMap)
        Rebuilds the Extensible HardwareMap from scratch based on a given HardwareMap. This modifies the reference to the maps within inside this HardwareMap, but not the reference to the HardwareMap itself.
        Parameters:
        hwMap - a valid non-null HardwareMap that contains what this needs to build on

      • get

        @NotNull
public <T extends com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.HardwareDevice> T get(java.lang.String name)
                                                                           throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Searches through this to find a HardwareDevice with the given name. If there are more than one HardwareDevices with the given name, the first one found is the one returned.
        Parameters:
        name - a non-null, non-empty String to use to match to a HardwareDevice
        Returns:
        a HardwareDevice with the given name
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the HardwareDevice cannot be cast to the correct form
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if name is null or empty
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the a name with the given name cannot be found

      • wire

        public Wire wire(java.lang.String name,
                 byte address)
          throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Builds a new Wire to allow for a better usage of I2C Devices. This method only looks at devices represented by i2cDevices()
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the I2C to use, as known by i2cDevices()
        address - the respective I2C address for the I2C Device
        Returns:
        a new Wire with the I2C Device represented by the given name
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if name is empty or null
        See Also:
        Wire, I2cFactory, I2cDevice
